Please add basic functionality that appears to be missing. Allow an admin in the user interface to filter users that belong to a specific directory.

I specifically need to filter for users in the JIRA Internal Directory. I am shocked that seems so basic is missing. I know I can do this through the database but really - why would this not be available in the administration capabilities.


There are several items within JIRA now that I just don't understand why they have not been addressed. I get the feeling that the users are not taken seriously - not everyone that uses the tool or even those that administer the tool are developers. GUI is important in a software tool and basic functionality that can save admins and users time and effort should really be considered as important. Having to go and create a query in My SQL to do something as basic as limiting the list of users down by the directory they exist in seems ludicrous.

