Customer has raised a valid suggestion regarding how issues from previous and the following months are displayed.
 * In the calendar view, any deadlines that fall on days outside of the month being displayed, but within the range of days displayed (the calendar shows a few greyed out days from the previous month and the following month) are unfortunately not shown, which is confusing since it gives the impression that these days have no deadlines (while they might). From a UX point of view this is rather bad since the widget doesn't display the correct information unless one navigates to the next (or previous) month.

Displaying these issues will prevent confusion as users might immediately assume from the calendar that there are no deadlines in the first few days of the following month.

